  "datePublished": "2025-09-28",
  "description": "In American intellectual discourse, the prefix 'post-' consistently translates from temporal ('after') to oppositional ('against'). Three structural causes: Puritan covenant binary, compressed epistemic field, and Cold War sorting. Documented across five cases with a self-reinforcing feedback loop.",
